  readonly fontFamily?: string;
  readonly fontSize?: string;
}
```

The `ThemeColors` interface uses camelCase keys that map 1:1 to the CSS variable names (camelCase `cardForeground` maps to `--card-foreground`). A utility function `themeColorsToCssProperties` converts camelCase to kebab-case CSS variable names.

**Built-in themes:**

- `"t3-dark"` -- The current dark theme colors extracted from `@variant dark` in `index.css`, with `colorScheme: "dark"`. The values can use the same `oklch()` / `color-mix()` syntax as the CSS since these will be applied as inline CSS property values.
