# Theme System Implementation Plan

## Context

T3 Code currently has a simple light/dark/system toggle (`useTheme.ts`) that swaps a `.dark` CSS class on `<html>`. All UI components already consume CSS custom properties (`--background`, `--foreground`, `--primary`, etc.) defined in `index.css`. The goal is to replace this basic toggle with a richer theme system that supports named themes with full color palettes, font settings, and a visual theme selector with preview swatches.

## Files to Create/Modify

| File | Action |
|------|--------|
| `packages/shared/src/themes.ts` | **Create** — theme types, 3 built-in themes, lookup functions |
| `packages/shared/src/themes.test.ts` | **Create** — unit tests for theme module |
| `packages/shared/package.json` | **Modify** — add `./themes` subpath export |
| `apps/web/src/hooks/useTheme.ts` | **Modify** — replace with theme-system-aware hook |
| `apps/web/src/components/ThemeSelector.tsx` | **Create** — theme selector with color swatches |
| `apps/web/src/routes/_chat.settings.tsx` | **Modify** — use ThemeSelector in Appearance section |

---

## Step 1: `packages/shared/src/themes.ts` (new)

Pure TypeScript, no React, no DOM, no Effect — follows the `git.ts` pattern.

### Types

```typescript
export interface ThemeColors {
  background: string;
  foreground: string;
  accent: string;
  sidebar: string;
  editor: string;
  terminal: string;
  statusBar: string;
}

export interface Theme {
  readonly id: string;
  readonly name: string;
  readonly colorScheme: "light" | "dark";   // drives .dark class for Tailwind
  readonly colors: ThemeColors;
  readonly fontFamily: string;
  readonly fontSize: number;
}
```

`colorScheme` is needed so the web app knows whether to add `.dark` to `<html>` (Tailwind's `@custom-variant dark` depends on it).

### Built-in themes

All color values must be **self-contained CSS color literals** (`oklch()`, `#hex`, `rgb()`, `rgba()`) — never Tailwind variable references like `var(--color-neutral-800)` since they're only available inside the Tailwind context and can't be used for JS-applied inline styles or swatch previews.

```
t3-dark (default):
  colorScheme: "dark"
  background:  oklch(0.145 0.005 286)    — near-black neutral
  foreground:  oklch(0.93 0.005 286)     — near-white
  accent:      oklch(0.588 0.217 264)    — the existing blue-purple primary
  sidebar:     oklch(0.13 0.005 286)     — slightly darker than bg
  editor:      oklch(0.145 0.005 286)    — matches background
  terminal:    oklch(0.115 0.005 286)    — deeper black
  statusBar:   oklch(0.175 0.005 286)    — slightly lighter than bg
  fontFamily:  "DM Sans", -apple-system, ... system-ui, sans-serif
  fontSize:    14

t3-light:
  colorScheme: "light"
  background:  #ffffff
  foreground:  oklch(0.269 0.006 286)    — neutral-800
  accent:      oklch(0.488 0.217 264)    — existing light-mode primary
  sidebar:     oklch(0.97 0.002 286)     — very light gray
  editor:      #ffffff
  terminal:    oklch(0.97 0.002 286)
  statusBar:   oklch(0.95 0.003 286)
  fontFamily:  same as dark
  fontSize:    14

t3-midnight:
  colorScheme: "dark"
  background:  oklch(0.16 0.03 270)      — deep navy
  foreground:  oklch(0.92 0.01 270)      — bluish white
  accent:      oklch(0.65 0.25 275)      — brighter indigo
