```

### Exported functions

```typescript
export function getTheme(id: string): Theme | undefined
export function listThemes(): readonly Theme[]
```

`listThemes()` returns the frozen built-in array. `getTheme()` does a `.find()` by id.

### CSS variable mapping helper

```typescript
/** Maps a Theme's colors to CSS custom property names for document.documentElement.style */
export function themeToCssProperties(theme: Theme): Record<string, string> {
  // Returns e.g. { "--t3-background": "...", "--t3-foreground": "...", ... }
  // Also maps to existing app CSS vars:
  //   colors.background → "--background"
  //   colors.foreground → "--foreground"
  //   colors.accent     → "--accent", "--primary", "--ring"
  //   colors.sidebar    → "--sidebar"     (new)
  //   colors.editor     → "--editor"      (new)
  //   colors.terminal   → "--terminal"    (new)
  //   colors.statusBar  → "--status-bar"  (new)
  // Derives secondary/muted/card/popover/border/input from the base colors:
  //   --card, --popover → slightly lighter/darker than background
  //   --secondary, --muted → low-opacity foreground overlay
  //   --border, --input → low-opacity foreground overlay
  //   --primary-foreground, --accent-foreground, etc. → derived from colorScheme
}
```

This function computes the full set of CSS variables from the 7 theme colors + colorScheme, so all existing Tailwind-based components continue to work. It returns a flat `Record<string, string>` — the web app applies it to `document.documentElement.style`.

