## Step 1: `packages/shared/src/themes.ts` (new)

Pure TypeScript, no React, no DOM, no Effect — follows the `git.ts` pattern.

### Types

```typescript
export interface ThemeColors {
  background: string;
  foreground: string;
  accent: string;
  sidebar: string;
  editor: string;
  terminal: string;
  statusBar: string;
}

export interface Theme {
  readonly id: string;
  readonly name: string;
  readonly colorScheme: "light" | "dark";   // drives .dark class for Tailwind
  readonly colors: ThemeColors;
  readonly fontFamily: string;
  readonly fontSize: number;
}
```

`colorScheme` is needed so the web app knows whether to add `.dark` to `<html>` (Tailwind's `@custom-variant dark` depends on it).

### Built-in themes

All color values must be **self-contained CSS color literals** (`oklch()`, `#hex`, `rgb()`, `rgba()`) — never Tailwind variable references like `var(--color-neutral-800)` since they're only available inside the Tailwind context and can't be used for JS-applied inline styles or swatch previews.

```
